Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.83,0:00:03.24,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}宇宙就是这样\NThe cosmos is all there is
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.58,0:00:04.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}过去是这样\Nor ever was,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.28,0:00:06.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}以后还是这样\Nor ever will be
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.73,0:00:09.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}跟我来\NCome with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.53,0:00:12.50,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}30多年前\NA generation ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.54,0:00:14.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}宇航员卡尔·赛根站在这里\Nthe astronomer Carl Sagan stood here
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.94,0:00:16.91,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,带领全世界数亿人\Nand launched hundreds of millions of us
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.94,0:00:18.91,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,进行了一场历险\Non a great adventure...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.94,0:00:22.74,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,用科学去探索宇宙的奥秘\Nthe exploration of the universe revealed by science.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.78,0:00:25.75,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是时候再次探险了\NIt's time to get going again.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.78,0:00:28.75,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这场即将开始的旅行会向我们展示\NWe're about to begin a journey that will take us
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.79,0:00:31.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从最微小的到无穷大的\Nfrom the infinitesimal to the infinite,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.89,0:00:34.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从时间的开始到遥远的未来\Nfrom the dawn of time to the distant future.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.89,0:00:39.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我们会探索不同的世界和星系\NWe'll explore galaxies and suns and worlds,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.23,0:00:42.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}在时间和空间的组合中畅游\Nsurf the gravity waves of space-time,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.27,0:00:45.60,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}接触生活在火中和冰中的生物\Nencounter beings that live in fire and ice,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.64,0:00:49.37,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}探索永恒不灭的星系\Nexplore the planets of stars that never die,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.41,0:00:51.97,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}了解和恒星一样大的原子\Ndiscover atoms as massive as suns
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.01,0:00:56.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}还有比原子还小的宇宙\Nand universes smaller than atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.11,0:00:59.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这也是关于人类的故事\NCosmos{\i1} is also a story about us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.28,0:01:03.42,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}这也是先人们对星空研究的史诗长篇\NIt's the saga of how wandering{\i0}\N{\i1}bands of hunters and gatherers
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.45,0:01:08.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}这也是先人们对星空研究的史诗长篇\Nfound their way to the stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.16,0:01:11.93,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}众多英雄共同谱写的史诗\None adventure with many heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.64,0:01:24.11,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们需要想象力来完成这次历险\NTo make this journey,we'll need imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.14,0:01:26.44,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但仅靠想象力是不够的\NBut imagination alone is not enough
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.48,0:01:29.65,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为大自然的真实样子是超乎想象的神奇\Nbecause the reality of nature is far more wondrous
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.68,0:01:32.01,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为大自然的真实样子是超乎想象的神奇\Nthan anything we can imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.05,0:01:39.69,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,几代研究人员的努力使这次的历险成为可能\NThis adventure is made possible\Nby generations of searchers
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.72,0:01:43.19,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们严格地坚持一套简单的规则\Nstrictly adhering to a simple set of rules...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.23,0:01:47.03,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以试验和观察结果检验观点\Ntest ideas by experiment and observation,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.06,0:01:49.97,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以通过检验的观点为基础\Nbuild on those ideas\Nthat pass the test,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.00,0:01:52.20,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,摒弃未通过检验的\Nreject the ones that fail,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.24,0:01:54.84,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,用证据说话\Nfollow the evidence wherever it leads
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.87,0:01:57.51,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并对一切存疑\Nand question everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.54,0:02:00.01,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,接受这些规则\NAccept these terms,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.04,0:02:03.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是你的宇宙\Nand the cosmos is yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.01,0:02:07.32,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟我来吧\NNow come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.68,0:03:45.82,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,中文翻译 @SaltyEggPain\NSync and corrections by n17t01 \Nwww.addic7ed.com
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.30,0:04:04.30,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在这艘想象之船中\NIn this ship of the Imagination,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.30,0:04:06.90,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不受空间和时间的限制\Nfree from the shackles of space and time,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.94,0:04:09.97,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以去任何地方\Nwe can go anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.01,0:04:12.24,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你想知道我们身处太空何处\NIf you want to see where we are in space,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.28,0:04:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要看向窗外\Njust look out the front window.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.38,0:04:23.02,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以时间来说，过去就在我们脚下\NIn the dimension of time, the past lies beneath us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.32,0:04:29.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是地球2.5亿年前的样子\NHere's what Earth looked like 250 million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.13,0:04:35.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抬头，就可以看到未来的样子\NIf you want to see the future, look up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.73,0:04:41.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是2.5亿年后可能的样子\NAnd this is how it could appear 250 million years from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.37,0:04:43.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我们要尝试\NIf we're going to be venturing out
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.84,0:04:46.68,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在极度广阔的宇宙中联系\Ninto the farthest reaches of the cosmos,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.71,0:04:49.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们需要知道自己的宇宙地址\Nwe need to know our{\i1} cosmic{\i0} address,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.65,0:04:53.35,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是我们地址的第一行\Nand this is the first line of that address.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.35,0:04:57.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,地球
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.54,0:05:18.91,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我们现在离开地球，这个我们仅有的家园\NWe're leaving the Earth,{\i0}\N{\i1}the only home we've ever known,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.94,0:05:23.35,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}向极度宽广的宇宙进发\Nfor the farthest reaches of the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.38,0:05:31.25,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我们最近的邻居，月球，没有大气层\NOur nearest neighbor, the Moon, has no sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.29,0:05:34.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}没有海洋，没有生命\Nno ocean, no life...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.72,0:05:38.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}只有天体撞击的伤痕\Njust the scars of cosmic impacts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.11,0:05:54.08,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}太阳为风和浪提供能量\NOur star powers the wind and the waves
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.11,0:05:57.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}为地球表面一切的生物提供能量\Nand all the life on the surface of our world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.95,0:06:00.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}整个太阳系都被太阳的引力场所包围\NThe Sun holds all the worlds of the solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.55,0:06:05.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}从水星开始\Nin its gravitational embrace, starting with Mercury...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.64,0:06:27.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}到云层覆盖的金星，失控温室效应\N...to cloud-covered Venus,{\i0}\N{\i1}where runaway greenhouse effect
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.58,0:06:31.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}把它变成一处炼狱\Nhas turned it into a kind of hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.12,0:06:38.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}火星\NMars...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.96,0:06:43.93,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}表面积和地球相近\Na world with as much land as Earth itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.14,0:06:59.44,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}一条岩石似的小行星带\NA belt of rocky asteroids circles the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.48,0:07:01.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}在火星和木星的轨道间围绕太阳运行\Nbetween the orbits of Mars and Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.46,0:07:17.76,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}木星被四个大卫星和几十个小卫星环绕\NWith its four giant moons{\i0}\N{\i1}and dozens of smaller ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.79,0:07:21.26,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}木星好像拥有自己的太阳系一般\NJupiter is like its own little solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.30,0:07:25.70,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}它的质量超过所有其他行星的总和\NIt has more mass than\Nall the other planets combined.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.35,0:07:39.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}木星的大红斑\NJupiter's Great Red Spot...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.35,0:07:42.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}它是一个比地球大3倍的古老风暴\Na hurricane three times the size of our whole planet
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.52,0:07:46.16,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}已经存在了几百年之久\Nthat's been raging for centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.51,0:08:10.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}土星宛如太阳系中皇冠上的明珠\NThe crown jewel of our solar system, Saturn,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.41,0:08:13.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}被无数运行轨道和缓慢翻滚的雪球所环绕\Nringed by freeways of countless orbiting
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.68,0:08:16.05,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}被无数运行轨道和缓慢翻滚的雪球所环绕\Nand slowly tumbling snowballs...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.09,0:08:20.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}每个雪球都是一个小月亮\Nevery snowball, a little moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.72,0:08:53.89,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}天王星\NUranus...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.92,0:08:55.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}还有海王星\Nand Neptune,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.93,0:09:00.23,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}这颗古人未知的最偏远的行星\Nthe outermost planets,{\i0}\N{\i1}unknown to the ancients
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.26,0:09:05.30,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}直到望远镜发明后才被发现\Nand only discovered after{\i0}\N{\i1}the invention of the telescope.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.44,0:09:08.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}在这最偏远的行星之外\NBeyond the outermost planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.84,0:09:13.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}还有成千上万的冰冻世界\Nthere's a swarm of tens{\i0}\N{\i1}of thousands of frozen worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.03,0:09:33.66,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}冥王星就是其中一个\NAnd Pluto is one them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.34,0:09:48.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}在我们所有的航天器中\NOf all our spacecraft,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.78,0:09:52.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}这是离家最远的一个\Nthis is the one that's traveled{\i0}\N{\i1}farthest from home...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.12,0:09:55.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}旅行者1号\NVoyager 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.35,0:09:59.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}她承载着我们发向未来的信息\NShe bears a message to\Na billion years from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.02,0:10:02.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}关于我们是谁\Nsomething of who we were,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.79,0:10:04.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我们的体会\Nhow we felt
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.96,0:10:06.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}以及我们创作的音乐\Nand the music we made.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.18,0:10:20.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}浩瀚宇宙海洋中\NThe deeper waters
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.04,0:10:21.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}更深层的水流里\Nof this vast cosmic ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.91,0:10:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}存在着数不尽的世界\Nand their numberless worlds lie ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.64,0:10:41.51,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}从这里看，太阳好像和其他星星并无两样\NFrom out here, the Sun may look like\Njust another star.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.54,0:10:43.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但它的引力场依然影响着\NBut it still exerts its gravitational hold
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.98,0:10:46.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,数万亿的冰冻彗星\Non a trillion frozen comets,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.38,0:10:49.11,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}还有太阳系中那些形成于大约50亿年前的\Nleftovers from the formation of the solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.15,0:10:51.95,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}其他所有组成部分\Nnearly five billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.98,0:10:54.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我们称之为 奥尔特云\NIt's called the Oort Cloud.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.62,0:10:57.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}以前从没有人见过，也不可能见过\NNo one has ever seen it before,{\i0}\N{\i1}nor could they,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.36,0:10:59.59,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}因为这些天体\Nbecause each one of these little worlds
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.63,0:11:01.83,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}与它最近的邻居之间的距离\Nis as far from its nearest neighbor
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.86,0:11:05.46,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}和地球与土星的距离差不多 (12-16亿公里）\Nas Earth is from Saturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.50,0:11:09.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个包含太阳系的巨大彗星云团\NThis enormous cloud of comets\Nencloses the solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.33,0:11:13.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是我们宇宙地址的第二行\Nwhich is the second line\Nof our cosmic address.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.14,0:11:16.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,地球\N太阳系
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.04,0:11:21.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我们有能力探测其他星系的行星\NWe've only been able to detect{\i0}\N{\i1}the planets of other stars
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.71,0:11:23.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}也就是最近几十年的事情\Nfor a few decades,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.72,0:11:27.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}但是我们已经知道行星的数量是很多的\Nbut we already know{\i0}\N{\i1}that planets are plentiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.49,0:11:30.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}比恒星的数量要多得多\Nthey outnumber the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.16,0:11:33.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}几乎所有的行星都和地球很不一样\NAlmost all of them will be very different from Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.59,0:11:36.06,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}不适合生物生存\Nand hostile to life as we know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.09,0:11:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}但是我们对于生物又有多少了解呢？\NBut what do we know about life?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.50,0:11:41.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}目前我们只接触过一种\NWe've met only one kind so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.57,0:11:43.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}地球生物\NEarthlife.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.54,0:11:44.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看到什么了吗？\NSee anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.87,0:11:46.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只是空荡荡的太空 对吗\NJust empty space, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.87,0:11:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人类的眼睛只能看到\NHuman eyes see only a sliver of the light
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.68,0:11:51.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙中得一丝光亮\Nthat shines in the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.68,0:11:55.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是科技让我们可以看到肉眼无法看到的\NBut science gives us the power\Nto see what our senses cannot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.91,0:11:58.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,夜视镜可以让我们看见红外线\NInfrared is the kind of light made visible
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.68,0:12:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,夜视镜可以让我们看见红外线\Nby night-vision goggles.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.72,0:12:03.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,向黑暗中发射一个红外感应器\NThrow an infrared sensor across the darkness...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.79,0:12:06.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,流浪行星\NRogue planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.43,0:12:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不绕恒星公转的行星\NWorld without a sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.60,0:12:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的银河中有数十亿颗游荡在永恒的黑夜中\NOur galaxy has billions of them,\Nadrift in perpetual night.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.07,0:12:18.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在他们原本的星系诞生时的混乱中\NThey're orphans, cast away\Nfrom their mother stars
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.64,0:12:22.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们像孤儿一样失去了恒星母亲\Nduring the chaotic birth\Nof their native star systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.81,0:12:26.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}流浪行星有着熔岩般的内核\NRogue planets are molten at the core
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.48,0:12:28.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}但是冰冻的表面\Nbut frozen at the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.48,0:12:30.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}在这些极端区域的中间\NThere may be oceans of liquid water
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.48,0:12:33.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}也许存在着大洋般的液体水\Nin the zone between those extremes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.06,0:12:41.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}谁又能知道水中生活着什么东西呢\NWho knows what might be swimming there?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.43,0:12:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是银河的红外线显示图\NThis is what the Milky Way\Nlooks like in infrared.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.64,0:12:52.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每个小点，不仅仅是那些明亮的\NEvery single dot,\Nnot just the bright ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.74,0:12:54.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都是一颗恒星\Nis a star.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.94,0:12:56.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,多少恒星？\NHow many stars?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.94,0:12:58.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,多少行星？\NHow many worlds?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.94,0:13:01.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,多少中生命存在的方式？\NHow many ways of being alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.45,0:13:04.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我们身处图片中的何处？\NWhere are{\i0} we{\i1} in this picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.45,0:13:06.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}看到那条螺旋臂了吗？\NSee that trailing outer arm?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.92,0:13:09.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我们就在那里\NThat's where we live...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.12,0:13:12.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}距离中心3万光年\Nabout 30,000 light-years{\i0}\N{\i1}from the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.36,0:13:14.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}银河系\NThe Milky Way Galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.09,0:13:17.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我们宇宙地址的下一行\Nis the next line of our cosmic address.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.43,0:13:19.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我们现在离家十万光年\NWe're now a hundred thousand{\i0}\N{\i1}light-years from home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.83,0:13:23.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}光波，存在的速度最快的东西\NIt would take light,{\i0}\N{\i1}the fastest thing there is,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.10,0:13:26.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}要花10万年才能从地球到达我们这里\Na hundred thousand years{\i0}\N{\i1}to reach us from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.71,0:13:32.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是仙女座螺旋星系\NThis is the Great Spiral in Andromeda,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.14,0:13:34.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,银河系的隔壁邻居\Nthe galaxy next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.15,0:13:36.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们将这两大星系\NWe call our two giant galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.15,0:13:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和一些较小的星系称为\Nand a smattering of smaller ones
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.15,0:13:40.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,本星系群\Nthe "local group."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.58,0:13:46.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,地球，太阳系，银河系，本星系群
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.16,0:13:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}从这里已经看不到银河系了\NCan't even find our home galaxy from out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.50,0:13:55.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}它只是室女座超星系团中得几千份之一\NIt's just one of thousands{\i0}\N{\i1}in the Virgo Supercluster.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.73,0:13:57.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}以这个比例来说\NOn this scale,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.67,0:14:01.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们所看到的，哪怕最小的点\Nall the objects we see,\Nincluding the tiniest dots,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.31,0:14:03.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都是一个星系\Nare galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.14,0:14:05.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}每个星系包含几十亿颗恒星\NEach galaxy contains billions of suns
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.71,0:14:07.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}和数不清的行星世界\Nand countless worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.81,0:14:11.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}然而，整个室女座超星系团\NYet, the entire Virgo Supercluster itself
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.48,0:14:14.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}只是我们宇宙的一个极小组成部分\Nforms but a tiny part of our universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.39,0:14:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}这是我们已知的最大范围的宇宙\NThis is the cosmos{\i0}\N{\i1}on the grandest scale we know...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.39,0:14:23.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}一张由数以千亿的星系组成的大网\Na network of a hundred billion galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.73,0:14:27.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}也是我们宇宙地址的最后一行\NIt's the last line of our cosmic address...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.20,0:14:29.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}截止目前\Nfor now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.20,0:14:30.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,地球，太阳系，银河系，本星系群\N室女座超星系团，可观测宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.77,0:14:32.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}可观测宇宙\NObservable{\i0} universe?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.27,0:14:34.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么意思\NWhat does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.17,0:14:36.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,即使我们在想象之船中\NEven for us, in our\NShip of the Imagination,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.94,0:14:40.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在时空中所能看到的也是有限的\Nthere's a limit to how far\Nwe can see in space-time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.58,0:14:42.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是我们的宇宙水平线\NIt's our cosmic horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.02,0:14:46.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一部分的宇宙处于水平线之下\NBeyond that horizon\Nlie parts of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.12,0:14:48.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,离我们实在太遥远了\Nthat are too far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.29,0:14:50.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在仅有的时间里\NThere hasn't been enough time
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.29,0:14:53.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在宇宙138亿年的历史中\Nin the 13.8 billion year history of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.39,0:14:55.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,光线还来不及传递过来\Nfor their light to have reached us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.93,0:15:01.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}很多人猜测，所有的这一切\NMany of us suspect{\i0}\N{\i1}that all of this...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.37,0:15:05.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}所有的行星，恒星，星系，星团\Nall the worlds, stars,{\i0}\N{\i1}galaxies and clusters
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.60,0:15:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我们的可观测宇宙中得一切\Nin our observable universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.04,0:15:12.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}只是其他宇宙中得沧海一粟\Nis but one tiny bubble in an infinite ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.78,0:15:14.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}只是其他宇宙中得沧海一粟\Nof other universes...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.42,0:15:18.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}多重宇宙论\N...a multiverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.92,0:15:22.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}宇宙之上的宇宙\NUniverse upon universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.72,0:15:25.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}没有尽头的世界\NWorlds without end.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.00,0:15:32.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,感觉很渺小吗\NFeeling a little small?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.10,0:15:35.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,相对宇宙来说 我们确实很渺小\NWell, in the context\Nof the cosmos, we{\i1} are small.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.60,0:15:38.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们或许只是生活在这浩瀚宇宙中\NWe may just be little guys\Nliving on a speck of dust,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.94,0:15:41.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,漂浮的灰尘粒上的小不点\Nafloat in a staggering immensity,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.34,0:15:43.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我们并不坐井观天\Nbut we don't think small.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.48,0:15:46.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在的宇宙论诞生并不久远\NThis cosmic perspective is relatively new.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.95,0:15:51.22,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,仅仅400年前，我们尚未认识\NA mere four centuries ago,\Nour tiny world was oblivious
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.25,0:15:53.22,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,自身世界以外的宇宙\Nto the rest of the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.25,0:15:55.22,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那时没有望远镜\NThere were no telescopes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.25,0:15:58.99,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只能看到我们肉眼可见的部分\NThe universe was only what you\Ncould see with the naked eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.02,0:16:01.09,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在1599年\NBack in 1599,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.13,0:16:04.46,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所有人都认为太阳，行球，星星\Neveryone knew that the Sun,\Nplanets and stars
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.50,0:16:08.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只是环绕地球的亮光\Nwere just lights in the sky\Nthat revolved around the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.53,0:16:12.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我们是宇宙的中心\Nand that we were the center{\i0}\N{\i1}of a little universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.60,0:16:15.37,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}由上帝为我们创造的宇宙\Na universe made for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.94,0:16:19.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}当时全世界只有一个人\NThere was only one man{\i0}\N{\i1}on the whole planet
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.35,0:16:22.18,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}想象着一个无尽的浩瀚宇宙\Nwho envisioned{\i0}\N{\i1}an infinitely grander cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.21,0:16:24.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}他是怎么度过他的1600年除夕？\NAnd how was{\i0} he{\i1} spending{\i0}\N{\i1}New Year's Eve
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.78,0:16:27.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}他是怎么度过他的1600年除夕？\Nof the year 1600?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.95,0:16:30.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}当然是在监狱里\NWhy, in prison, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.85,0:16:40.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}生命中总有那么一天\NThere comes a time in our lives
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.05,0:16:43.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们发现自己并不是宇宙的中心\Nwhen we first realize we're not\Nthe center of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.32,0:16:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们以外还有更广大的世界\Nthat we belong to something\Nmuch greater than ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.56,0:16:48.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是成长\NIt's part of growing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.56,0:16:50.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每个人都会经历\NAnd as it happens to each of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.83,0:16:53.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的文明也在16世纪经历过这样的成长\Nso it began to happen to our civilization
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.17,0:16:55.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的文明也在16世纪经历过这样的成长\Nin the 16th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.17,0:16:57.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}想象一下望远镜问世之前\NImagine a world before telescopes,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.07,0:16:59.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我们只能靠肉眼观察这个宇宙\Nwhen the universe{\i0}\N{\i1}was only what you could see
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.34,0:17:00.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我们只能靠肉眼观察这个宇宙\Nwith the naked eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.87,0:17:04.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}很显然地球是静止不动的\NIt was obvious that Earth was motionless,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.08,0:17:05.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}天空中得一切\Nand that everything in the heavens...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.81,0:17:08.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}太阳 月亮 星星 星球\Nthe Sun, the Moon, the stars, the planets...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.15,0:17:10.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}都围绕着我们运行  然后\Nrevolved around us... and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.02,0:17:13.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一位名叫哥白尼的波兰天文学家兼牧师\Na Polish astronomer and priest named Copernicus
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.32,0:17:17.29,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,提出一个地球并非中心的激进假想\Nmade a radical proposal.\NThe Earth was not the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.32,0:17:19.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,地球只是和其他星星一样的行星\NIt was just one of the planets,\Nand, like them,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.83,0:17:21.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,绕着太阳旋转\Nit revolved around the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.83,0:17:25.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很多人 例如宗教改革发起人马丁·路德\NMany, like the Protestant reformer Martin Luther,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.16,0:17:28.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,认为这是在对圣经的可耻侮辱\Ntook this idea as a scandalous\Naffront to Scripture.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.17,0:17:30.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们震怒了\NThey were horrified.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.44,0:17:34.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是另一个人却认为哥白尼说的不全面\NBut for one man,\NCopernicus didn't go far enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.91,0:17:38.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他叫焦尔达诺·布鲁诺
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.04,0:17:40.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}他生性反叛\Nand he was a natural-born rebel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.55,0:17:43.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}他渴望打破这狭隘宇宙的枷锁\NHe longed to bust out of that{\i0}\N{\i1}cramped little universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.75,0:17:46.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}在那不勒斯做道明会的修道士时\NEven as a young Dominican monk in Naples,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.22,0:17:48.39,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}他就与这个世界格格不入\Nhe was a misfit.{\i0}\N{\i1}This was a time
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.42,0:17:50.72,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}当时在意大利没有思想的自由\Nwhen there was{\i0}\N{\i1}no freedom of thought in Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.76,0:17:52.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}但是布鲁诺渴望了解\NBut Bruno hungered to know
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.19,0:17:53.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}关于上帝创世的一切\Neverything about God's creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.03,0:17:56.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}他阅读了被教廷禁止的书籍\NHe dared to read the books{\i0}\N{\i1}banned by the Church,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.80,0:17:58.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}从此踏上了不归路\Nand that was his undoing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.60,0:18:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}这些书籍中\NIn one of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.63,0:18:04.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}有一本作者是1500年前的古罗马人\N（物性论 - 卢克莱修）\Nan ancient Roman, a man dead{\i0}\N{\i1}for more than 1,500 years
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.77,0:18:07.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}想他描述了一个更广阔的宇宙\Nwhispered to him of a universe far greater,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.74,0:18:10.74,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}广阔的犹如他的上帝一般\None as boundless as his idea of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.88,0:18:16.85,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}卢克莱修让他的读者\NLucretius asked the reader
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.88,0:18:19.25,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}想象站在宇宙的边缘\Nto imagine standing{\i0}\N{\i1}at the edge of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.29,0:18:21.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}向外射出一支箭\Nand shooting an arrow outward.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.29,0:18:23.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}如果箭继续前进，那么很明显\NIf the arrow keeps going,{\i0}\N{\i1}then clearly,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.59,0:18:26.46,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}宇宙继续向所谓的边缘以外延伸\Nthe universe extends beyond{\i0}\N{\i1}what you thought was the edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.49,0:18:28.89,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}但是如果箭不继续前进\NBut if the arrow doesn't keep going...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.93,0:18:31.60,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}比方说 撞在一堵墙上\Nsay it hits a wall...{\i0}\N{\i1}then that wall must lie
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.63,0:18:34.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}那么墙必然是处在所谓的边缘之外\Nbeyond what you thought{\i0}\N{\i1}was the edge of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.60,0:18:37.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}那么如果你站在这堵墙上向外射箭\NNow if you stand on{\i0} that{\i1} wall{\i0}\N{\i1}and shoot another arrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.94,0:18:40.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}也只有这相同的两个结果\Nthere are only the same{\i0}\N{\i1}two possible outcomes...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.67,0:18:43.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}要么是飞入无尽的太空\Nit either flies forever out into space,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.08,0:18:45.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}要么是撞在某个障碍物上\Nor it hits some boundary
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.08,0:18:47.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}然后你又可以站在上面射出另一支箭\Nwhere you can stand and shoot{\i0}\N{\i1}yet another arrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.85,0:18:50.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}无论如何 宇宙是没有界限的\NEither way, the universe is unbounded.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.45,0:18:53.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}宇宙必然是无尽的\NThe cosmos must be infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.75,0:18:56.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}布鲁诺深以为然\NThis made perfect sense to Bruno.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.26,0:18:58.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}他崇拜的上帝是全能的\NThe God he worshiped was infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.62,0:19:02.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}所以他断定 上帝创造的宇宙怎会不是无穷\NSo how, he reasoned, could{\i0}\N{\i1}Creation be anything less?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.11,0:19:20.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}那是他的最后一份稳定工作\NIt was the last steady job he ever had.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.36,0:19:32.76,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}后来 当他30岁时\NAnd then, when he was 30,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.79,0:19:36.43,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}他的一个幻觉从此改变他的一生\Nhe had the vision that sealed his fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.46,0:19:38.93,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}在这个梦中 他认识到了\NIn this dream, he awakened to a world
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.96,0:19:42.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}一个包含在一群行星中的世界\Nenclosed inside a confining bowl of stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.03,0:19:45.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}就是他那个时代的宇宙\NThis was the cosmos of Bruno's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.49,0:20:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}他感到一阵不舒服的害怕\NHe experienced a sickening moment of fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.06,0:20:07.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}就像脚下的一切\Nas if the bottom of everything
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.59,0:20:10.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}向下坠落\Nwas falling away beneath his feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.23,0:20:12.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}但是他鼓起了勇气\NBut he summoned up his courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.74,0:20:23.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我展开自信的翅膀飞向太空\NI spread confident wings to space
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.58,0:20:27.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}向上高飞至无尽的天空\Nand soared toward the infinite,{\i0}\N{\i1}leaving far behind me
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.18,0:20:30.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}将一切的压力抛在身后\Nwhat others strained to see{\i0}\N{\i1}from a distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.55,0:20:33.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}这里没有上 没有下 没有边界\NHere, there was no up, no down, no edge,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.95,0:20:35.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}没有中心\Nno center.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.52,0:20:38.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我看见太阳和其他星星一样\NI saw that the Sun{\i0}\N{\i1}was just another star,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.96,0:20:42.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}还有其他被行星伴随着的恒星\Nand the stars were other Suns,{\i0}\N{\i1}each escorted by other Earths
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.93,0:20:44.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}就像我们的太阳\Nlike our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.56,0:20:47.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}这巨大的启示对他就如同\NThe revelation of this immensity was like
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.87,0:20:49.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}坠入爱河\Nfalling in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.77,0:20:54.74,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}布鲁诺变成了一个传教士\NBruno became an evangelist,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.77,0:20:58.18,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}他在欧洲各地宣扬他的宇宙无限论\Nspreading the gospel{\i0}\N{\i1}of infinity throughout Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.21,0:21:01.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}他以为其他上帝的追随者会同样接受\NHe assumed that other lovers{\i0}\N{\i1}of God would naturally embrace
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.81,0:21:04.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}这个对于创世的伟大并荣耀的观点\Nthis grander and more glorious view of Creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.88,0:21:07.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我太傻了\NWhat a fool I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.96,0:21:11.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}在他的祖国 他被罗马天主教会开除教籍\NHe was excommunicated
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.66,0:21:13.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}在他的祖国 他被罗马天主教会开除教籍\Nby the Roman Catholic Church in his homeland,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.59,0:21:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}他不仅被瑞士加尔文长老会驱逐出境\Nexpelled by the Calvinists in Switzerland,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.06,0:21:18.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}还被德国的路德教派驱逐出境\Nand by the Lutherans in Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.30,0:21:21.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}布鲁诺接受了一份邀请\NBruno jumped at an invitation
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.33,0:21:24.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}去英国牛津大学讲课\Nto lecture at Oxford, in England.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.57,0:21:27.41,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}他认为这是一个机会\NAt last, he thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.44,0:21:31.08,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}可以与他类似的人分享他的观点\Na chance to share his vision{\i0}\N{\i1}with an audience of his peers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.18,0:21:38.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我来介绍一个对于宇宙的崭新看法\NI have come to present\Na new vision of the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.28,0:21:41.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哥白尼是对的\NCopernicus was right to argue that our world
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.35,0:21:43.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的世界并不是宇宙的中心\Nis{\i1} not{\i0} the center of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.09,0:21:45.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,地球绕着太阳旋转\NThe Earth goes around the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.16,0:21:47.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它和其他行星一样\NIt's a planet, just like the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.66,0:21:49.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但哥白尼只是曙光\NBut Copernicus was only the dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.76,0:21:51.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而我为你们带来日出\NI bring you the sunrise.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.33,0:21:55.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那些星星和我们炙热的太阳一样\NThe stars are other fiery suns,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.43,0:21:57.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,由和地球一样的天体组成\Nmade of the same substance as the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.67,0:22:00.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们也有自己的含水的地球\Nand they have their own watery earths,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.71,0:22:03.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上面有着和我们一样高贵的动物植物\Nwith plants and animals\Nno less noble than our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.81,0:22:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是疯了还是太蠢\NAre you mad or merely ignorant?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.11,0:22:07.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,总所周知只有一个世界\NEveryone knows there is only one world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.88,0:22:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是错误的\NWhat everyone knows is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.38,0:22:13.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们全能的上帝创造了一个无边无际的宇宙\NOur infinite God has created\Na boundless universe
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.39,0:22:15.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其中包含了无数的星球\Nwith an infinite number of worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.29,0:22:17.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们那的人没读过亚里斯多德的书吗\NDo they not read Aristotle where you come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.32,0:22:19.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或者是圣经吗\NOr even the Bible?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.06,0:22:23.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我请求你摒弃老旧和传统的信仰和权威\NI beg you, reject antiquity, tradition, faith, and authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.70,0:22:24.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让我们重新认识\NLet us begin anew,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.00,0:22:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,质疑我们以为已经被证实的一切\Nby doubting everything we assume
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.03,0:22:28.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,异端者\N- has been proven.\N- Heretic!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.17,0:22:29.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,异教徒\NInfidel!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.24,0:22:31.10,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们信仰的上帝太小了\NYour God is too small.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.68,0:22:39.04,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}明智的人本应该从中吸取了教训\NA wiser man would have learned his lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.08,0:22:42.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可惜布鲁诺并不是那个人\NBut Bruno was not such a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.42,0:22:46.65,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不停的宣扬自己观点\NHe couldn't keep his soaring\Nvision of the cosmos to himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.69,0:22:49.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尽管这会带来沉痛的代价\Ndespite the fact that the penalty for doing so
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.66,0:22:52.66,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在他的那个时代，代价是如此的残酷\Nin his world was the most vicious form
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.69,0:22:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,无情和不寻常的惩罚\Nof cruel and unusual punishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.80,0:23:01.47,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,焦尔达诺·布鲁诺生活的那个时代\NGiordano Bruno lived at a time when there was no such thing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.50,0:23:03.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有政教分离\Nas the separation of church and state,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.47,0:23:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有言论自由神圣不可侵犯\Nor the notion that freedom\Nof speech was a sacred right
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.04,0:23:07.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有言论自由神圣不可侵犯\Nof every individual.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.01,0:23:10.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,表达与传统信仰相悖的观点\NExpressing an idea that didn't\Nconform to traditional belief
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.88,0:23:13.48,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,会带来极大的麻烦\Ncould land you in deep trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.48,0:23:18.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,布鲁诺不顾一切地回到了意大利\NRecklessly, Bruno returned to Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.18,0:23:19.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许是想家了\NMaybe he was homesick.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.85,0:23:23.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可是他必须知道\NBut still, he must have known\Nthat his homeland
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.12,0:23:25.19,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的祖国对他来说\Nwas one of the most dangerous\Nplaces in Europe
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.22,0:23:26.96,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是最危险的国家\Nhe could possibly go.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.99,0:23:30.03,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,由罗马天主教会管辖的宗教法庭\NThe Roman Catholic Church\Nmaintained a system of courts
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.06,0:23:31.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被称为异端裁判所\Nknown as the Inquisition,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.90,0:23:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它唯一职责就是审查和折磨\Nand its sole purpose was to investigate and torment
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.47,0:23:39.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,与教会持有不同声音和观点的人\Nanyone who dared voice views that differed from theirs.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.38,0:23:46.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,布鲁诺很快就被思想警察抓获\NIt wasn't long before Bruno fell into the clutches
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.35,0:23:48.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,布鲁诺很快就被思想警察抓获\Nof the thought police.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.25,0:23:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}这位信奉无限宇宙的流浪者\NThis wanderer, who worshiped{\i0}\N{\i1}an infinite universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.92,0:24:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}在八年的监狱生涯中饱受煎熬\Nlanguished in confinement for eight years.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.09,0:24:01.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}尽管受尽残酷的审讯\NThrough relentless interrogations,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.93,0:24:04.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}他依然不愿放弃他的观点\Nhe stubbornly refused to renounce his views.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.66,0:24:06.20,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}为什么教会要花\NWhy was the Church willing
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.23,0:24:09.90,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}如此长的时间来折磨布鲁诺\Nto go to such lengths to torment Bruno?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.94,0:24:11.97,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}他们在害怕什么\NWhat were they afraid of?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.00,0:24:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}如果布鲁诺是对的 那么这些圣典\NIf Bruno was right, then the sacred books
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.24,0:24:17.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}还有教会的权威\Nand the authority of the Church
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.41,0:24:20.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}都会受到质疑\Nwould be open to question.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.78,0:24:22.48,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}最终 异端裁判所的红衣主教们\NFinally, the cardinals of the Inquisition
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.52,0:24:24.42,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}做出了他们的判决\Nrendered their verdict.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.45,0:24:26.02,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你有罪\NYou are found guilty
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.05,0:24:28.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你质疑圣父圣子圣灵三位一体\Nof questioning the Holy Trinity
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.92,0:24:31.59,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你质疑耶稣基督的神威\Nand the divinity of Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.62,0:24:34.89,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你相信上帝的怒火不会永远\NOf believing that God's wrath is not eternal,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.93,0:24:36.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所有人都会被宽恕\Nthat everyone will be saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.43,0:24:41.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你断言其他世界存在的主张\NOf asserting the existence of other worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.37,0:24:45.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你写的所有书\NAll of the books you have written
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.30,0:24:48.77,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都会在圣彼得广场前焚毁\Nwill be gathered up and burned in St. Peter's Square.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.81,0:24:52.38,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尊敬的大人 8年的监禁\NReverend Father, these eight years of confinement
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.41,0:24:53.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,给了我很多时间去反省\Nhave given me much time to reflect.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.98,0:24:54.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后呢\NSo...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.98,0:24:56.35,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要放弃你的主张吗\Nyou will recant?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.38,0:24:58.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我对造物主的爱和崇敬\NMy love and reverence for the Creator
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.38,0:25:02.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,激发我对全能的上帝的认识\Ninspires in me the vision of an infinite Creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.06,0:25:05.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你会被移交到罗马总督\NYou shall be turned over to the Governor of Rome
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.66,0:25:09.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,予以执行相应地惩罚\Nto administer the appropriate punishment
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.06,0:25:11.13,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你拒不忏悔的话\Nfor those who will not repent.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.23,0:25:17.14,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可能你宣布这个判决时的恐惧\NIt may be that you are more afraid
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.17,0:25:20.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,比我听到判决的时候更厉害\Nto deliver this judgment than I am to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.64,0:26:30.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,布鲁诺殉难的10年后\NTen years after Bruno's martyrdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.91,0:26:33.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,伽利略通过望远镜\NGalileo first looked through a telescope,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.38,0:26:36.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,发现布鲁诺的学说确实没错\Nrealizing that Bruno had been right all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.05,0:26:38.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,银河系是由肉眼看不到的无数恒星组成\NThe Milky Way was made of countless stars
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.82,0:26:40.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,银河系是由肉眼看不到的无数恒星组成\Ninvisible to the naked eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.55,0:26:44.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天空中的某些光亮其实是其他的行星\Nand some of those lights in the \Nsky were actually other worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.52,0:26:46.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,布鲁诺不是科学家\NBruno was no scientist.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.83,0:26:49.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他只是侥幸猜中了\NHis vision of the cosmos was a lucky guess,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.33,0:26:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为没有证据支持他\Nbecause he had no evidence to support it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.83,0:26:55.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就和其他猜想一样 也有可能不对\NLike most guesses, it could\Nwell have turned out wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.10,0:26:57.67,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是这个观点一旦散播出去\NBut once the idea was in the air,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.70,0:26:59.74,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它就给了其他人一个方向\Nit gave others a target to aim at.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.77,0:27:01.37,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哪怕只是为了反驳\NIf only to disprove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.41,0:27:07.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}布鲁诺大致理解了太空的浩瀚无垠\NBruno glimpsed the vastness of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.11,0:27:11.88,*Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}但他对于时间的惊人无际没有丝毫概念\NBut he had no inkling of the{\i0}\N{\i1}staggering immensity of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.46,0:27:18.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,寿命很少超过一个世纪的普通人\NHow can we humans, who rarely\Nlive more than a century,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.56,0:27:21.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么可能去理解宇宙的历史\Nhope to grasp the vast expanse of time
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.36,0:27:23.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像浩瀚宽阔的时间长河\Nthat is the history of the cosmos?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.60,0:27:28.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙诞生于138亿年前\NThe universe is 13.8 thousand million years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.40,0:27:30.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了更好地想象宇宙的历史\NIn order to imagine all of cosmic time,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.80,0:27:34.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们把它压缩成12个月的年历\Nlet's compress it into a single calendar year.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.57,0:27:51.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,年历上的1月1号是宇宙诞生的日子\NThe cosmic calendar begins on January 1st\Nwith the birth of our universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.59,0:27:54.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,年历上包含了从那以后经历的所有时间\NIt contains everything that's\Nhappened since then,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.28,0:27:55.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一直到现在\Nup to now,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.37,0:27:59.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在这个年历上的12月31号午夜\Nwhich on this calendar\Nis midnight December 31st.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.92,0:28:03.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,按照这个比例 每个月代表10亿年\NOn this scale, every month\Nrepresents about a billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.89,0:28:08.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每天代表将就4千万年\NEvery day represents nearly 40 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.45,0:28:10.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让我们尽可能地回到过去\NLet's go back as far as we can,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.34,0:28:13.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,回到宇宙最开始的时刻\Nto the very first moment of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.43,0:28:18.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1月1号 宇宙大爆炸\NJanuary 1st, the Big Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.16,0:28:32.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是我们所能看到最早的时间\NIt's as far back as we can see in time...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.96,0:28:34.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,目前而言\Nfor now.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.79,0:28:40.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,整个宇宙形成于一个比原子还小的点\NOur entire universe emerged from\Na point smaller than a single atom.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.62,0:28:43.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,空间在密度极大温度极高的状态下爆炸\NSpace itself exploded in a cosmic fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.62,0:28:45.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,由此开始了宇宙的扩张\Nlaunching the expansion of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.99,0:28:48.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并诞生了所有的能量\Nand giving birth to all the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.39,0:28:50.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,已经产生所有我们已知的事物\Nand all the matter we know today.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.36,0:28:52.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听上去很疯狂\NI know that sounds crazy,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.69,0:28:54.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是我们有很强力的观测证据\Nbut there's strong observational evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.66,0:28:56.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来支持宇宙大爆炸理论\Nto support the Big Bang theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.30,0:28:58.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,证据还有氦元素在宇宙中的比例\NAnd it includes the amount\Nof helium in the cosmos
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.80,0:29:02.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以及爆炸残留的发光无线电频谱\Nand the glow of radio waves\Nleft over from the explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.47,0:29:04.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爆炸后宇宙开始冷却\NAs it expanded, the universe cooled,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.97,0:29:09.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其间有2亿年左右的黑暗\Nand there was darkness\Nfor about 200 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.88,0:29:12.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,万有引力将气体集聚并且加热\NGravity was pulling together\Nclumps of gas and heating them
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.85,0:29:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,直到第一批恒星发出亮光\Nuntil the first stars burst into light
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.85,0:29:18.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,相当于1月10号\Non January 10th.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.99,0:29:26.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1月13号 这些恒星开始结合\NOn January 13th, these stars coalesced
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.83,0:29:31.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,形成第一批小星系\Ninto the first small galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.73,0:29:34.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}这些星系融合成更大的星系\NThese galaxies merged to form still larger ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.57,0:29:37.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}包括我们的银河系\Nincluding our own Milky Way,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.94,0:29:42.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}产生于110亿年左右\Nwhich formed about 11 billion years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.41,0:29:45.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}就是宇宙年历上得3月15号\Non March 15th of the cosmic year.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.12,0:29:49.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,数千亿的恒星中\NHundreds of billions of suns.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.62,0:29:51.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哪个是我们的太阳\NWhich one is ours?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.45,0:29:53.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,此时尚未诞生\NIt's not yet born.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.69,0:29:58.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它将从其他恒星的灰烬中产生\NIt will rise from the ashes of other stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.19,0:30:01.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}看到这些犹如闪光灯般的亮光吗\NSee those lights flashing like paparazzi?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.43,0:30:03.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}每一个都是超新星\NEach one is a supernova,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.90,0:30:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}一颗超大恒星的耀眼爆炸\Nthe blazing death of a giant star.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.07,0:30:10.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}恒星消亡和诞生的地方\NStars die and are born{\i0}\N{\i1}in places like this one...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.47,0:30:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我们称为星星苗圃 （分子云）\Na stellar nursery.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.37,0:30:14.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}他们像雨滴般\NThey condense like raindrops
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.08,0:30:16.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}从巨大的气态和灰尘云中凝结\Nfrom giant clouds of gas and dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.75,0:30:19.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}他们温度高的可以把原子中的原子核\NThey get so hot that the nuclei of the atoms
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.75,0:30:22.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}融合在一起\Nfuse together deep within them
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.28,0:30:25.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}从而产生了我们呼吸的氧气 肌肉中的碳元素\Nto make the oxygen we breathe,{\i0}\N{\i1}the carbon in our muscles,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.49,0:30:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}骨头中的钙元素 血中的铁元素\Nthe calcium in our bones,{\i0}\N{\i1}the iron in our blood,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.96,0:30:30.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}所有的这一切都产生于\Nall of it was cooked
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.76,0:30:34.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}从此消亡的恒星炙热的内心\Nin the fiery hearts of long-vanished stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.26,0:30:37.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你 我 所有人\NYou, me, everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.00,0:30:42.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们都是由星辰物质组成\Nwe are made of star stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.24,0:30:46.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}星辰物质被不断循环和浓缩\NThis star stuff is recycled and enriched,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.57,0:30:48.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}一遍又一遍\Nagain and again,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.14,0:30:50.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}经过几代恒星的诞生消亡\Nthrough succeeding generations of stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.08,0:30:57.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}离我们的太阳诞生还有多久\NHow much longer until the birth of our Sun?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.49,0:30:59.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}很长时间\NA long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.29,0:31:00.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们太阳的第一次发光\NIt won't begin to shine
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.59,0:31:03.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还要再等60亿年\Nfor another six billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.13,0:31:08.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}太阳的生日是8月31号\NOur Sun's birthday is August 31st
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.13,0:31:09.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}在这个宇宙年历上\Non the Cosmic Calendar...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.47,0:31:14.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}45亿年前\N...four and a half billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.77,0:31:17.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像太阳系中其他行星\NAs with the other worlds of our solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.27,0:31:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,地球在一堆气体和灰尘中产生\NEarth was formed from a disk of gas and dust
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.38,0:31:22.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,绕着新生的太阳运行\Norbiting the newborn Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.54,0:31:25.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,反复的碰撞产生了一个发光的球状碎片\NRepeated collisions produced\Na growing ball of debris.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.39,0:31:33.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}看到那个小行星了吗\NSee that asteroid?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.82,0:31:35.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}不是那个\NNo, not that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.16,0:31:36.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}那边的那个\NThe one over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.86,0:31:40.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我们的存在归功于它旁边的引力\NWe exist because the gravity{\i0}\N{\i1}of that one next to it
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.63,0:31:43.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}把它轻轻向左推了一英寸\Njust nudged it an inch to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.80,0:31:45.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}一英寸有很大的区别吗\NWhat difference could an inch make
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.83,0:31:47.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}按照太阳系的比例来说\Non the scale the solar system?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.90,0:31:50.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}稍等 你马上就能看到\NJust wait, you'll see.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.37,0:31:54.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}在最初的10亿年里\NThe Earth took one hell of a beating
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.21,0:31:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}地球饱受摧残\Nin its first billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.48,0:32:02.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}任由轨道上的碎片撞击和融合\NFragments of orbiting debris collided and coalesced,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.38,0:32:04.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}直到他们形成了我们的月亮\Nuntil they snowballed to form our Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.16,0:32:10.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}月亮是那个暴力纪元的纪念品\NThe Moon is a souvenir of that violent epoch.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.73,0:32:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}如果你站在远古地球的表面\NIf you stood on the surface{\i0}\N{\i1}of that long ago Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.76,0:32:16.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}月亮会看上去比现在亮100倍\Nthe Moon would have looked{\i0}\N{\i1}a hundred times brighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.50,0:32:18.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}那时月亮离我们近10倍\NIt was ten times closer back then,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.70,0:32:23.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}被比现在更强大的引力场吸引着\Nlocked in a much more intimate{\i0}\N{\i1}gravitational embrace.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.44,0:32:26.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}地球冷却下来 海洋形成了\NAs the Earth cooled, seas began to form.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.41,0:32:29.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}海浪比现在高1000倍\NThe tides were a thousand times higher then.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.51,0:32:32.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}经过极漫长的时间 潮汐的摩擦力\NOver the eons,{\i0}\N{\i1}tidal friction within Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.75,0:32:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}将月球推远\Npushed the Moon away.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.72,0:32:43.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,生命差不多在这个时候诞生\NLife began somewhere around here,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.46,0:32:45.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,9月21号\NSeptember 21st,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.56,0:32:48.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在地球上的35亿年前\Nthree and a half billion\Nyears ago on our little world.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.63,0:32:50.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们依然不知道生命如何起源\NWe still don't know how life got started.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.43,0:32:52.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们只是知道\NFor all we know,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.10,0:32:54.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有可能是来自银河系的其他地方\Nit may have come from\Nanother part of the Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.14,0:32:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,生命的起源\NThe origin of life
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.97,0:32:59.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是最伟大的未知科学奇迹之一\Nis one of the greatest\Nunsolved mysteries of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.81,0:33:04.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,生命的演变\NThat's life cooking,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.88,0:33:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}一切生物化学的进化\Nevolving all the biochemical recipes
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.45,0:33:11.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}充满了无与伦比的复杂活动\Nfor its incredibly complex activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.15,0:33:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}到了11月9号 生命开始呼吸 移动\NBy November 9th,{\i0}\N{\i1}life was breathing, moving,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.73,0:33:20.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}进食和对周遭环境做出反应\Neating, responding to its environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.63,0:33:23.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}多亏了这些有开拓性的微生物\NWe owe a lot to those pioneering microbes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.57,0:33:25.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}没错 就是这些不起眼的家伙\NOh, yeah... one other thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.63,0:33:28.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}他们还发明了繁殖\NThey also invented sex.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.41,0:33:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,12月17号 很特别的一天\NDecember 17th was quite a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.61,0:33:37.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,海洋中生命的发展开始腾飞\NLife in the sea really took off,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.08,0:33:39.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,形形色色的大型植物和动物\Nit was exploding with a diversity
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.25,0:33:41.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爆炸式的发展\Nof larger plants and animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.25,0:33:46.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}提塔利克鱼是最早冒险登陆的动物之一\NTiktaalik{\i0} was one of the first\Nanimals to venture onto land.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.26,0:33:51.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,感觉肯定像是造访另一个星球\NIt must have felt like visiting another planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.13,0:33:55.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,森林  恐龙\NForests, dinosaurs,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.53,0:33:57.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鸟类 昆虫\Nbirds, insects,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.87,0:34:01.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都在12月的最后一周进化而来\Nthey all evolved in the final week of December.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.27,0:34:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第一朵花\NThe first flower...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.14,0:34:07.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在12月28号 盛开\Nbloomed on December 28th.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.85,0:34:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,随着古森林的成长死亡\NAs these ancient forests grew and died
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.62,0:34:15.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并被深埋进地下\Nand sank beneath the surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.62,0:34:18.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们的残骸形成了煤\Ntheir remains transformed into coal.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.49,0:34:21.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,3亿年后\N300 million years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.12,0:34:24.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人类燃烧这些煤来推动文明的发展\Nwe humans are burning most of that coal to power
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.46,0:34:27.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,同时也使我们的文明陷入危机\Nand imperil our civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.50,0:34:33.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还记得那颗在太阳系形成时的\NRemember that asteroid back in the formation
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.90,0:34:35.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小行星吗\Nof the solar system...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.57,0:34:37.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那颗被轻轻推动的小行星\Nthe one that got nudged a little to the left?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.74,0:34:40.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它来了\NWell, here it comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.08,0:34:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}早晨6点24分\NIt's 6:24 AM
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.54,0:34:46.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}宇宙年历上的12月30号\Non December 30th on the Cosmic Calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.86,0:34:55.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在1亿年的时间里\NFor more than a hundred million years,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.82,0:34:58.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恐龙曾是这个地球的统治者\Nthe dinosaurs were lords of the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.06,0:35:00.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当我们的祖先 小型哺乳动物\Nwhile our ancestors, small mammals,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.83,0:35:02.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,战战兢兢地在地面爬来爬去的时候\Nscurried fearfully underfoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.00,0:35:05.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这颗小行星改变了一切\NThe asteroid changed all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.40,0:35:07.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,假如它没有被推动\NSuppose it hadn't been nudged at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.24,0:35:09.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它会完全和地球擦肩而过\NIt would have missed the Earth entirely,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.07,0:35:11.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恐龙恐怕依然存在\Nand for all we know, the\Ndinosaurs might still be here
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.37,0:35:12.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我们不会\Nbut we wouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.01,0:35:15.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是极端突发状况的好例子\NThis is a good example of the extreme contingency,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.01,0:35:18.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,生存的偶然性\Nthe chance nature, of existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.42,0:35:23.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}宇宙已经诞生了超过\NThe universe is already more than 13 and a half
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.72,0:35:25.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,135亿年\Nbillion years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.12,0:35:26.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人类仍未出现\NStill no sign of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.96,0:35:31.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在这个年历代表的时间长河中\NIn the vast ocean of time that this calendar represents,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.13,0:35:34.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人类在最后一小时进化\Nwe humans only evolved within the last hour
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.23,0:35:39.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙年历中的最后一天\Nof the last day of the cosmic year.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.61,0:35:48.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}11点59分46秒\N11:59 and 46 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.38,0:35:52.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,全部有记载的历史发生在最后的14秒里\NAll of recorded history occupies only the last 14 seconds,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.61,0:35:55.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你听说过得所有人\Nand every person you've ever heard of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.38,0:35:57.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,存在于这个点的某个位置\Nlived somewhere in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.25,0:36:03.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所有这些国王 战役 迁徙 发明\NAll those kings and battles,\Nmigrations and inventions,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.23,0:36:07.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,战争和爱情 历史书中的一切\Nwars and loves, everything in the history books
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.73,0:36:09.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都发生在这宇宙年历中的最后几秒\Nhappened here, in the last seconds
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.80,0:36:11.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都发生在这宇宙年历中的最后几秒\Nof the Cosmic Calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.90,0:36:14.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但如果我们想要研究\NBut if we want to explore
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.10,0:36:16.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙年历中这段极短的时间\Nsuch a brief moment of cosmic time...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.27,0:36:21.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们必须改变比例\N...we'll have to change scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.21,0:36:40.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们是这个宇宙的新丁\NWe are newcomers to the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.61,0:36:45.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的历史仅仅从宇宙年的最后一晚开始\NOur own story only begins on the\Nlast night of the cosmic year.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.05,0:36:48.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,新年前夜的9点45分\NIt's 9:45 on New Year's Eve.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.45,0:36:50.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,350万年前\NThree and a half million years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.89,0:36:54.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你我的祖先留下这些足迹\Nour ancestors, yours and mine, left these traces.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.16,0:36:59.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们站了起来和他们区别开来\NWe stood up, and parted ways from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.83,0:37:01.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,自从我们直立行走\NOnce we were standing on two feet,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.76,0:37:04.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的双眼不在迷恋地面\Nour eyes were no longer fixated on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.93,0:37:08.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在我们可以自由的探索奇迹\NNow we were free to look up in wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.17,0:37:13.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人类存在的大部分时间里\NFor the longest part of human existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.68,0:37:17.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,比方说最近的4万代人\Nsay the last 40,000 generations,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.45,0:37:19.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们曾是流浪者\Nwe were wanderers,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.28,0:37:22.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,猎人和采集者混住在一起\Nliving in small bands of hunters and gatherers,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.48,0:37:25.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,制作工具 生火\Nmaking tools, controlling fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.15,0:37:27.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,给事物起名字\Nnaming things,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.16,0:37:31.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都发生在宇宙年历的最后一个小时里\Nall within the last hour of the Cosmic Calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.63,0:37:43.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们必须改变比例去继续探寻\NTo find out what happens next, we'll have to change scale
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.14,0:37:46.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最后一晚的最后一分钟\Nto see the last minute of the last night
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.34,0:37:49.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,发生了什么\Nof the cosmic year.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.38,0:37:51.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,11:59
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.38,0:37:54.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以宇宙时间比例来说我们太太太年轻了\NWe're so very young on the time scale of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.05,0:37:56.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们甚至还没开始画出第一张画\Nthat we didn't start painting our first pictures
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.68,0:38:00.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,直到宇宙年历的最后60秒\Nuntil the last 60 seconds of the cosmic year,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.29,0:38:03.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只不过是3万年前\Na mere 30,000 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.03,0:38:14.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我们发明了天文学\NThis is when we invented astronomy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.64,0:38:17.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}事实上我们都是天文学家的后裔\NIn fact, we're all descended from astronomers.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.84,0:38:21.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我们的生存要依靠研究星星\NOur survival depended on{\i0}\N{\i1}knowing how to read the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.24,0:38:23.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}用来预测冬天的到来\Nin order to predict the coming of the winter
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.58,0:38:26.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}以及兽群的迁徙\Nand the migration of the wild herds.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.21,0:38:29.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}然后大约1万年前\NAnd then, around 10,000 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.22,0:38:32.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我们的生活方式迎来了变革\Nthere began a revolution in the way we lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.22,0:38:35.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我们的祖先学会了如何改变周围环境\NOur ancestors learned{\i0}\N{\i1}how to shape their environment,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.49,0:38:37.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}栽培植物 驯养动物\Ntaming wild plants and animals,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.89,0:38:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}耕作土地 定居下来\Ncultivating land and settling down.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.90,0:38:43.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}这改变了一切\NThis changed everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.50,0:38:45.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}有史以来第一次\NFor the first time in our history,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.50,0:38:48.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我们可以拥有超过我们负重能力的东西\Nwe had more stuff than we could carry.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.90,0:38:51.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我们需要把这些数量记录下来\NWe needed a way to keep track of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.34,0:38:53.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}午夜前的14秒\NAt 14 seconds to midnight,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.54,0:38:57.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}大约6千年前 我们发明了书写\Nor about 6,000 years ago, we invented writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.05,0:38:59.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}随后不久我们就开始记录其他东西\NAnd it wasn't long before we started recording
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.55,0:39:01.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}不仅仅是粮食的数量\Nmore than bushels of grain.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.28,0:39:03.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}书写让我们保存我们的想法\NWriting allowed us to save our thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.28,0:39:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}并且跨越时间和空间的传播它们\Nand send them much further in space and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.55,0:39:08.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}泥板上的细小印记\NTiny markings on a clay tablet
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.96,0:39:12.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}成了我们征服有限的生命的手段\Nbecame a means for us to vanquish mortality.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.23,0:39:15.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}震撼了整个世界\NIt shook the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.36,0:39:18.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}摩西出生于7秒之前\NMoses was born seven seconds ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.47,0:39:21.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}释迦摩尼 6秒前\NBuddha, six seconds ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.40,0:39:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}耶稣基督 5秒前\NJesus, five seconds ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.31,0:39:27.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}穆罕穆德 3秒前\NMohammed, three seconds ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.74,0:39:31.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}不到2秒前 不论好坏\NIt was not even two seconds ago that, for better or worse,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.15,0:39:34.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}地球一边的人类发现了地球的另一边\Nthe two halves of the Earth discovered each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.48,0:39:36.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}仅仅在最后的一秒钟里\NAnd it was only in the very last second
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.75,0:39:39.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我们开始使用科学\Nof the Cosmic Calendar that we began to use science
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.75,0:39:42.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}去揭示大自然的秘密和规则\Nto reveal nature's secrets and her laws.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.92,0:39:45.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}科学方法是如此的强大\NThe scientific method is so powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.66,0:39:47.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}只用了4个世纪的时间\Nthat in a mere four centuries,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.66,0:39:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}就从伽利略第一次看向望远镜\Nit has taken us from Galileo's first look through a telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.00,0:39:54.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}到人类在月球上留下足迹\Nat another world to leaving our footprints on the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.50,0:39:58.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}它让我们可以越过时间和空间\NIt allowed us to look out across space and time
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.01,0:40:04.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}去观察我们在宇宙时空中的位置\Nto discover where and when we are in the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.78,0:40:09.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}我们有了了解宇宙本质的办法\NWe are a way for the cosmos to know itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.35,0:40:11.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,卡尔赛根30多年前带领我们进行了首次的\NCarl Sagan guided the maiden voyage of Cosmos
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.69,0:40:13.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙航行\Na generation ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.45,0:40:15.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不仅是20世纪最成功的\NHe was the most successful\Nscience communicator
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.66,0:40:17.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,科学传播者\Nof the 20th century,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.16,0:40:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也是一位首屈一指的科学家\Nbut he was first and foremost a scientist.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.93,0:40:23.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}卡尔为我们了解行星\NCarl contributed enormously
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.47,0:40:25.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}做出了极大的贡献\Nto our knowledge of the planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.67,0:40:28.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}他正确地预测了有沼气湖存在于\NHe correctly predicted the existence of methane lakes
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.67,0:40:30.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}木星的卫星 泰坦 土卫六上\Non Saturn's giant moon Titan.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.67,0:40:33.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}他指出早期地球的大气层中\NHe showed that the atmosphere of the early Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.98,0:40:36.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1} 必然含有强大的温室气体\Nmust have contained powerful greenhouse gases.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.95,0:40:40.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}他首先推断出火星上的季节变化\NHe was the first to understand{\i0}\N{\i1}that seasonal changes on Mars
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.95,0:40:43.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}是由沙尘暴引起\Nwere due to windblown dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.45,0:40:44.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}卡尔是一位\NCarl was a pioneer
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.02,0:40:46.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}在探索地球以外智慧生物领域的\Nin the search for extraterrestrial life
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.45,0:40:49.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}先行者\Nand intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.36,0:40:52.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}太空时代的最初40年里 每次主要的\NHe played a leading role in{\i0}\N{\i1}every major spacecraft mission
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.66,0:40:55.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}太阳系探索航天任务 他都担任了\Nto explore the solar system during the first 40 years
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.16,0:40:57.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}重要的职务\Nof the Space Age.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.30,0:41:02.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这还不是全部\NBut that's not all he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.41,0:41:08.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是卡尔的一本1975年的记事日历\NThis is Carl Sagan's own calendar from 1975.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.48,0:41:13.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我那时在做什么\NWho was I back then?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.52,0:41:16.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只是一个纽约的17岁男孩\NI was just a 17-year-old kid from the Bronx
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.35,0:41:18.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,梦想着可以成为科学家\Nwith dreams of becoming a scientist,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.75,0:41:22.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,世界上最著名的天文学家\Nand somehow the world's most\Nfamous astronomer found time
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.09,0:41:24.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,邀请我去纽约州\Nto invite me to Ithaca, in upstate New York,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.93,0:41:26.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和他共度一个周六\Nand spend a Saturday with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.73,0:41:30.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我记得那天下着雪\NI remember that snowy day like it was yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.17,0:41:31.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他来公车站接我\NHe met me at the bus stop
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.00,0:41:34.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,带我参观了他在康奈尔大学的实验室\Nand showed me his laboratory at Cornell University.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.90,0:41:39.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,卡尔从书桌后拿出这本书并在上面为我题字\NCarl reached behind his desk\Nand inscribed this book for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.08,0:41:45.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,至 尼尔 未来的天文学家\N"For Neil, a future astronomer.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.78,0:41:47.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,卡尔\NCarl." 
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.62,0:41:51.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,结束后 他开车送我去公车站\NAt the end of the day, he drove\Nme back to the bus station.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.05,0:41:53.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雪下得更大了\NThe snow was falling harder.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.05,0:41:55.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他写下他的电话号码 家里的电话\NHe wrote his phone number...\Nhis home phone number...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.06,0:41:58.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他把号码写在一张小纸片上 如果公车没有来\Non a scrap of paper and he said,\N"If the bus can't get through,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.56,0:42:02.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,打电话给我 就在我家过夜\Ncall me and spend the night at my home with my family."
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.40,0:42:05.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我当时已经决定要当一名科学家\NI already knew I wanted to become a scientist,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.23,0:42:07.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是那天下午 我认识到\Nbut that afternoon, I learned from Carl
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.64,0:42:09.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要做他那样的人\Nthe kind of person I wanted to become.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.90,0:42:13.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他帮助了我 还有其他很多人\NHe reached out to me and to countless others,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.58,0:42:18.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,激励我们去学习，教授，研究科学\Ninspiring so many of us to study, teach and do science.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.08,0:42:20.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,科学研究是一份需要合作的事业\NScience is a cooperative enterprise,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.48,0:42:22.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,持续几代人的时间\Nspanning the generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.88,0:42:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,火炬在老师和学生的手中传递\NIt's the passing of a torch from\Nteacher to student to teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.22,0:42:30.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一群伟大的思想从远古\Na community of minds\Nreaching back to antiquity
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.73,0:42:32.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,贯穿 直至未来的星空\Nand forward to the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.73,0:42:35.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在跟我来\NNow, come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.56,0:42:38.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的旅程开始了\NOur journey is just beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.05,0:43:14.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,中文翻译 @SaltyEggPain\NSync and corrections by n17t01\Nwww.addic7ed.com
